This rib re-expresses the Squad multi-agent runtime as a Keelson rib. It imports
none of the upstream code: its roster, genesis, and canvas-board machinery is a
clean-room port of the concepts below onto the `Rib` contract. It attaches
solely through the `Rib` contract from @keelson/shared. Attribution to the
upstream project whose vision this rib builds on follows.

==============================================================================
Concepts from: Squad (human-led teams of named agents for repo development)
==============================================================================

The rib's "squad" model — a human-led roster of named team members (a Lead, an
Engineer, a Reviewer, a Tester, or whatever the work needs) authored on demand
and directed against a repository — is ported from Squad, the originating
multi-agent runtime by Brady Gaster and contributors, used under the MIT
License. The roster and member model are re-typed for Keelson and driven by the
`Rib` contract; nothing is imported.

  Project: Squad
  Source:  https://github.com/bradygaster/squad
